      <p class="eyebrow-sub">FAQ</p>
      <h2>Sub-Zero wine cooler repair, common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>What does error 40140 or 40240 mean on my IW-24?</summary>
        <p>Temperature sensor (thermistor) fault, 40140 upper zone, 40240 lower zone. Sensor reading open, shorted, or inconsistent for more than 10 seconds. Diagnostic: check wiring first, test probe resistance (2,200 ohms at 40°F), replace if out of spec. Thermistor $175–$245. We don't swap control boards for these codes, 85% resolve at sensor level.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Why is humidity control so important?</summary>
        <p>Wine needs ~50% humidity to keep corks moist. Dry corks shrink, lose their seal, let oxygen in, oxidize the wine. Sub-Zero maintains humidity through sealed-system cooling profile + (on IW-30+) active humidity sensor. Door gasket leaks are the first cause of humidity problems. Gasket replacement $345–$485.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Dual-zone cools only one zone, what's wrong?</summary>
        <p>IW-24 and IW-30 use single compressor + three-way valve that alternates cooling between zones every 15–25 min. When valve sticks, one zone stays warm. Valve replacement $445–$620, specialized part we stock. 90-minute job.</p>
